subSubSection.paragraph:
Tytthus balli
: 
Carvalho and Southwood 1955
: 30 (descrip., n. comb.); 
Carvalho 1958
: 157 (cat.); 
Henry and Wheeler 1988
: 457 (cat.); 
Schuh 1995
: 248 (cat.).

Previously recorded only from imported roses (
Carvalho and Southwood 1955
), which undoubtedly is an incidental record. A. G. Wheeler and I have swept specimens from a salt marsh area containing mixed herbaceous vegetation and Spartina sp. [
Poaceae
].

This species was described from Jacksonville, Florida (
Knight 1931
), and later reported from an unspecified Mexican locality based on a specimen intercepted at Brownsville, Texas (
Carvalho and Southwood 1955
). The specimens listed below from Clay, Hidalgo, and Refugio counties represent the first authentic Texas records.
